  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">AWID (The Association for Women&apos;s Rights in Development) forum</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">OGB will contribute GBP10,000 to the Association for Women&apos;s Rights in Development (AWID) to support the running of their forum taking place in Brazil from 9 -11th September 2016. The funding will support the forum being as open and participatory as possible by providing access funding to those who could not otherwise afford to attend. The funding will enable AWID to meet the costs of the forum and supporting the participation of a wide range of activists. The Global Justice cross department team recently discussed this strategy and felt it would be a more strategic use of funds than funding individual partner organisations, since AWID have a coordinated process for applications to attend the conference and are aware of those most in need of support.</narrative>
  </description>
